\f0\b\fs28 WAVsToAAF \u8211  How to Use\

\f1\b0\fs24 \

\f0\b 1. Select Input\
\pard\pardeftab720\li360\fi-180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 \'95\tab 
\f0\b Single WAV
\f1\b0 : Click 
\f0\b "File..."
\f1\b0  and choose a single 
\f3 .wav
\f1  file\
\'95\tab 
\f0\b Folder of WAVs
\f1\b0 : Click 
\f0\b "Folder..."
\f1\b0  and choose a directory that contains WAV files (subfolders supported). The app writes one AAF per WAV.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \

\f0\b 2. Select Output Folder (optional)\
\pard\pardeftab720\li360\fi-180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 \'95\tab Click 
\f0\b "Browse..."
\f1\b0  to choose where AAF files will be written\
\'95\tab If you leave this blank the app will create an 
\f0\b AAFs
\f1\b0  folder next to your WAV directory and write AAFs there\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \

\f0\b 3. Set FPS (frames per second)\
\pard\pardeftab720\li360\fi-180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 \'95\tab Default is 
\f0\b 24
\f1\b0 . Choose from: 23.98, 23.976, 24, 25, 29.97, 30, 50, 59.94, 60\
\'95\tab 23.98 is normalized internally to 23.976\
\'95\tab Timecode fields include a StartTC_{fps}fps comment (e.g., StartTC_29_97fps)\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \

\f0\b 4. Audio Mode: Linked vs Embedded\
\pard\pardeftab720\li360\fi-180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 \'95\tab Unchecked (default): Linked AAFs reference original WAVs via NetworkLocator \u8211  small bins, fast relink\
\'95\tab Checked: Embedded AAFs are self-contained; portable but larger\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \

\f0\b 5. Run Conversion\
\pard\pardeftab720\li360\fi-180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 \'95\tab Click 
\f0\b "Run"
\f1\b0  \u8211  The app processes WAV files, extracts metadata (WAV header, BEXT, embedded XML, LIST/INFO, and UCS filename mapping), and writes AAF(s)\
\'95\tab A log pane displays progress and any skips/errors\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \

\f0\b 6. Open Output\
\pard\pardeftab720\li360\fi-180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 \'95\tab After a successful run, click 
\f0\b "Open AAF Location"
\f1\b0  to reveal the created AAF(s)\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \

\f0\b\fs28 What gets written\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 \'95\tab 
\f0\b AAF structure
\f1\b0 : MasterMob with comments; SourceMob with WAVE Descriptor; timeline slots sized to audio length; for linked mode, a NetworkLocator to the WAV file URL\
\'95\tab 
\f0\b Technicals
\f1\b0 : SampleRate, BitDepth, Channels, Number of Frames, Duration; Start/End timecode at selected FPS; track labels (A1, A1A2, A1A{n})\
\'95\tab 
\f0\b BEXT (if present)
\f1\b0 : Description, Originator, OriginatorReference, Origination Date/Time, Time Reference, UMID, Loudness\
\'95\tab 
\f0\b LIST-INFO (if present)
\f1\b0 : IART, ICMT, ICOP, ICRD, IENG, IGNR, IKEY, INAM, IPRD, ISBJ, ISFT, ISRC\
\'95\tab 
\f0\b XML (if present)
\f1\b0 : Keys from EBU Core, BWF MetaEdit, Pro Tools, or generic XML surfaced with prefixes (ebucore_, bwfmetaedit_, protools_, axml_, xml_)\
\'95\tab 
\f0\b UCS categorization
\f1\b0 : Primary category (Category, SubCategory, ID, Full Name) and match score\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \

\f0\b\fs28 Examples\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Create linked AAFs for a folder at 29.97 fps:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0

\f3 \cf0 python3 wav_to_aaf.py ./FX ./AAF --fps 29.97\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \

\f1 Create an embedded AAF for a single file at 23.976:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0

\f3 \cf0 python3 wav_to_aaf.py -f "Some File.wav" "Some File.aaf" --fps 23.976 --embed\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \

